---

  <section id="slots">
    <div class="col">
      <div class="eyebrow">02 · The slots</div>
      <h2>🔌 Real fillers nourish. Counterfeits just <em>quiet the alarm.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">Inside you there are slots — recurring needs: connection, rest, focus, intimacy, meaning, mastery. They aren't problems to be solved or hungers to be ashamed of. They're the design.</p>
      <p>You were built to be filled. When you ignore them, they get louder, then quiet — not because the need was met, but because something cheap moved in. Tap any slot below to see the balanced comparison between the real thing, the thin echo, how industries profit off the empty slot, and where the solution is actually found.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="slots-grid" id="slotsGrid">

      <!-- SLOT 01: Connection -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="true" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="true" style="--slot:#b6862f; view-transition-name: slot-1;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Connection</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need to be known by name in a room you keep coming back to.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>Friends on a couch at 1am, talking about nothing that matters and everything that does. The kitchen that fills with laughter on a Friday. A team that knows your jokes before you finish them. A neighbor who waves, and means it. Being missed when your chair is empty.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>400 followers. Twelve group chats you scroll but never speak in. A streamer whose name you know — who doesn't know yours. Reaction emojis. A “close friends” list of people you've never met.</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>Snapchat streaks</span><span>BeReal</span><span>muted group chats</span><span>parasocial streamers</span><span>follower counts</span><span>Close Friends stories</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>Connection is built by <b>time in a place with the same faces</b> — which is exactly what nothing can ship to you overnight. A standing table, a small group that notices your absence, a church you stay at long enough to be known.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the long table</span><span>the porch</span><span>the standing dinner</span><span>the front pew</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>Social platforms, creator memberships, parasocial streaming</b> — built to monetize the gap where a village used to be. The metric is engagement, not friendship, because a satisfied lonely person stops scrolling.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>Instagram</span><span>TikTok</span><span>Twitch</span><span>Discord</span><span>OnlyFans</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- SLOT 02: Rest -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="false" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="false" style="--slot:#7e9b6a; view-transition-name: slot-2;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Rest</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need for your whole system to trust that it's safe to stop.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>Lying in the grass with nothing in your hand and nowhere to be. A walk where you never once look down. Being bored long enough that the noise settles and you can hear yourself again. A nap with the phone in another room. The deep exhale of a day that was allowed to actually end.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>“Decompressing” with three hours of TikTok and ending up more tired than you started. Binge-watching past the point you enjoyed it. Sleepless scrolling. Falling asleep to a stranger's whisper.</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>doomscrolling in bed</span><span>Netflix autoplay</span><span>bed rotting</span><span>TikTok till 2am</span><span>YouTube rabbit holes</span><span>sleep-podcasts</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>A real Sabbath — one day where the work genuinely stops. Sleep protected like it's sacred, because it is. <b>Rest is received, not consumed</b>; it begins the moment you stop trying to manufacture it.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the Sabbath</span><span>the long walk</span><span>the empty hands</span><span>the dark room</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>Streaming, meditation and sleep apps, the wellness-retreat economy</b> — rest got turned into a product you consume, which is exactly why it leaves you emptier.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>Netflix</span><span>YouTube</span><span>TikTok</span><span>Calm</span><span>Headspace</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- SLOT 03: Focus -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="false" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="false" style="--slot:#c06a3a; view-transition-name: slot-3;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Focus</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need for one thing to mean enough that you stay with it.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>An hour on something genuinely hard, and the strange joy on the other side of it. A book that pulls you under so far you forget the room. A song heard all the way through. A single open tab and a quiet mind. The thing you made because you didn't quit at the boring part.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>Forty-seven seconds on one screen before you switch. 73 tab switches. The feeling that today already ended and you didn't do any of it. Twelve half-watched videos. A podcast at 2× you can't remember.</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>tab-switching</span><span>2× podcasts</span><span>study-with-me streams</span><span>hoarding Notion templates</span><span>energy drinks</span><span>phone every 47 sec</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>Long, undefended blocks of time. One craft pursued past the point of novelty. <b>Depth is the reward for staying</b> — and staying is a muscle the world is engineered to keep weak.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the deep block</span><span>the finished book</span><span>the one craft</span><span>the quiet desk</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>Productivity SaaS, “focus” apps, nootropics, course funnels</b> — one market sells you the cure for the distraction another market sells you.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>Notion</span><span>Forest</span><span>MasterClass</span><span>nootropics</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- SLOT 04: Intimacy -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="false" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="false" style="--slot:#a85a6b; view-transition-name: slot-4;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Intimacy</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need to be fully seen, and not run from.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>Telling one person the thing you were sure they'd judge — and finding out they didn't, and they stayed. Being known across years, through the parts you're not proud of. Someone who is still there after the hard conversation, holding your hand. Covenant: love that has decided, and doesn't keep its options open.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>Porn. An AI companion who agrees with everything. Trauma-dumping to strangers who never learn your name. Endless swiping. A situationship. DMs that simulate closeness at zero risk.</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>porn</span><span>AI girlfriends</span><span>endless swiping</span><span>situationships</span><span>sexting</span><span>sliding into DMs</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>One faithful friendship. A marriage that chose, and keeps choosing. A confessor who has heard the worst and not flinched. <b>Intimacy is the fruit of risk plus time</b>, and there is no shortcut that doesn't quietly remove one of them.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the one friend</span><span>the covenant</span><span>the long marriage</span><span>the kept secret</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>Dating apps, the adult-content economy, AI-companion apps</b> — they sell the feeling of being wanted while quietly profiting from your never quite landing it. A matched user is a churned user.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>Tinder</span><span>Hinge</span><span>Replika</span><span>Character.AI</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- SLOT 05: Meaning -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="false" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="false" style="--slot:#5f87a0; view-transition-name: slot-5;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Meaning</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need to pour yourself into something that would matter unwatched.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>Building something real and leaving it better than you found it. Raising a person. Serving something so much bigger than you that your name will be forgotten and you won't mind. Faith you'd keep even if it cost you everything. Work that would still matter if no one ever saw it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>Optimizing yourself. Picking a tribe to hate. Curating an identity instead of doing the work it describes. A personal brand with nothing underneath. Doomscrolling the news to feel “engaged.”</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>personal brand</span><span>hustle podcasts</span><span>rage-bait politics</span><span>doomscrolling the news</span><span>biohacking</span><span>main-character energy</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>A vocation, a calling, a people to serve, a God to answer to. <b>Meaning comes from being spent on something true</b> — not from being seen doing it. The unwatched version is the real one.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the calling</span><span>the child raised</span><span>the unseen work</span><span>the given life</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>The creator economy, self-optimization coaching, hustle culture</b> — purpose got unbundled into content and sold back to you as a course, a seminar, a membership that always points to the next tier.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>LinkedIn</span><span>X takes</span><span>coaching programs</span><span>biohacking</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- SLOT 06: Mastery -->
      <div class="slot" data-open="false" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-expanded="false" style="--slot:#8b5cf6; view-transition-name: slot-6;">
        <div class="slot-hint">+</div>
        <div class="slot-name">Mastery</div>
        <div class="slot-need">The need to become genuinely good at something through your own hands.</div>
        <div class="slot-detail"><div class="slot-detail-in">
          <div class="slot-cols">
            <div class="slot-col real">
              <h5>The Real Thing</h5>
              <p>Six months on the same hard skill, and the day your hands finally know it without being told. A craft that is actually yours. Calluses, repetitions, slow obvious progress you can feel. Making one real thing, well, and giving it to someone who needed it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake">
              <h5>The Thin Echo</h5>
              <p>Leveling up a game character. Watching someone else win on a stream. Reading about discipline instead of doing one hard thing. A 400-day streak that taught you nothing. Buying the gear instead of doing the reps.</p>
              <div class="slot-fakes">
                <span>Duolingo streaks</span><span>watching pros stream</span><span>gym-app stats, no reps</span><span>endless how-to videos</span><span>idle/clicker games</span><span>tutorial hell</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col real-found">
              <h5>Where It's Actually Found</h5>
              <p>An apprenticeship. A workshop, a kitchen, a garden, an instrument. <b>Competence is earned by embodied repetition</b> — there is dopamine in the real thing too, but it's on the far side of the work, not before it.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs">
                <span>the apprenticeship</span><span>the instrument</span><span>the garden bed</span><span>the made thing</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slot-col fake-industries">
              <h5>How they try selling it</h5>
              <p><b>Gaming progression systems, gamified “learning,” fitness-app subscriptions</b> — they borrow the feeling of getting better and detach it from any real skill. The dopamine of mastery with none of the mastery.</p>
              <div class="slot-egs gray">
                <span>Duolingo</span><span>Fortnite battle pass</span><span>Skillshare</span><span>gym apps</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 03 THE SPLIT -->
